                            <comment id="17412" author="hildenl" created="Thu, 27 Apr 2006 11:14:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Its been changed to proxy-target-class in M4 but isn&apos;t mentioned in the changelog.txt file.  The M4 reference guide refers to it as proxyTargetClass as well.   The spring-aop.xsd gets pulled from org/springframework/aop/config in spring-aop.jar, not the website.   Very annoying problem.  Took me a while to figure this out due to weak/misleading documentation.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17452" author="robh" created="Tue, 2 May 2006 02:11:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We decided on hyphenation as the official approach for all custom schemas as of M4. The schema on the website is outdated - I&apos;ll get that updated ASAP. AOP documentation is currently in progress - apologies for its transient state.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
